owl:Ontology.tawny:name: sbol
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: The OWL version of the SBOL data model

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The region specified by this Location is on the elements of a Sequence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: inline
owl:Class.tawny:name: inline
TopLevel
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Can be used to represent biological design components such as DNA, RNA and small molecules.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TopLevel

owl:Class.tawny:name: SMILES
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: SMILES sequence
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SMILES

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a ComponentInstance MAY be referred to by remote MapsTo objects.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: public
owl:Class.tawny:name: public
Participation
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Each Participation represents how a particular FunctionalComponent behaves in its parent Interaction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participation

owl:Class.tawny:name: Effector
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Effector small molecule
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Effector

owl:Class.tawny:name: ModuleDefinition
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a grouping of structural and functional entities in a biological design.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ModuleDefinition

owl:Class.tawny:name: overrideRoles
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that in the context of a Component, ignore any roles given for the included subComponentDefinition. Instead use only the set of zero or more roles given for this Component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: overrideRoles

owl:Class.tawny:name: GenericLocation
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: While the Range and Cut classes are best suited to specifying regions on Sequence objects with IUPAC encodings, the GenericLocation class is included as a starting point for specifying regions on Sequence objects with different encoding properties and potentially nonlinear structure. This class can also be used to set the orientation of a SequenceAnnotation and any associated Component when their parent ComponentDefinition is a partial design that lacks a Sequence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GenericLocation

owl:Class.tawny:name: Range
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Range object specifies a region via discrete, inclusive start and end positions that correspond to indices for characters in the elements String of a Sequence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Range

owl:Class.tawny:name: Restriction
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specifies relative positions of sub components in a design.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Restriction

owl:Class.tawny:name: mergeRoles
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates to use the union of the two sets: both the set of zero or more roles given for this Component as well as the set of zero or more roles given for the included subComponentDefinition.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: mergeRoles

owl:Class.tawny:name: Attachment
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The purpose of the Attachment class is to serve as a general container for data files, especially experimental data files. It provides a means for linking files and metadata to SBOL designs.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Attachment

owl:Class.tawny:name: precedes
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The position of the subject Component MUST precede that of the object Component. If each one is associated with a SequenceAnnotation, then the SequenceAnnotation associated with the subject Component MUST specify a region that starts before the region specified by the SequenceAnnotation associated with the object Component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: precedes

owl:Class.tawny:name: Identified
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents SBOL objects that can be identified uniquely using URIs.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identified

owl:Class.tawny:name: merge
owl:Class.rdfs:label: merge
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: In the context of the ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition that contains the owner of the MapsTo, all references to the local ComponentInstance or the remote ComponentInstance MUST dereference to both objects.
Any number of Component objects in the derived ComponentDefinition MAY have wasDerivedFroms properties that refer to the template Component.
owl:Class.tawny:name: zeroOrMore
owl:Class.rdfs:label: zeroOrMore

owl:Class.tawny:name: EngineeredGene
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: EngineeredGene DNA component
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EngineeredGene

owl:Class.tawny:name: GenericTopLevel
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The GenericTopLevel class is used to represent top-level entities whose purpose is to contain a set of annotations that are independent of any other class of SBOL object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GenericTopLevel

owl:Class.tawny:name: Terminator
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Terminator DNA component
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Terminator

owl:Class.tawny:name: Location
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Extended by the Range, Cut, and GenericLocation classes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Location

owl:Class.tawny:name: DNA
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: DNA component definition
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DNA

owl:Class.tawny:name: Gene
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Gene DNA component
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gene

owl:Class.tawny:name: Component
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Component class is used to compose ComponentDefinition objects into a structural hierarchy. For example,the ComponentDefinition of a gene could contain four Component objects: a promoter, RBS, CDS, and terminator. In turn, the ComponentDefinition of the promoter Component could contain Component objects defined as various operator sites.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Component

owl:Class.tawny:name: oppositeOrientationAs
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The subject and object Component objects MUST have opposite orientations. If each one is associated with a SequenceAnnotation, then the orientation URIs of the Location objects of one SequenceAnnotation MUST NOT be among those of the other SequenceAnnotation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: oppositeOrientationAs
inout
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the FunctionalComponent is both an input and output.
owl:Class.tawny:name: inout

owl:Class.rdfs:label: reverseComplement
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The region specified by this Location is on the reverse-complement translation of the elements of a Sequence. The exact nature of this translation depends on the encoding of the Sequence
owl:Class.tawny:name: reverseComplement
ComponentDefinition
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Can be used to represent biological design components such as DNA, RNA and small molecules.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ComponentDefinition
zeroOrOne
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: No more than one Component in the derived ComponentDefinition SHOULD have a wasDerivedFroms property that refers to the template Component.
owl:Class.tawny:name: zeroOrOne
CombinatorialDerivationStrategy
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specifies strategy types for combinatorial derivations.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CombinatorialDerivationStrategy

owl:Class.tawny:name: Operator
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operator DNA component
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Operator

owl:Class.tawny:name: Sequence
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The purpose of the Sequence class is to represent the primary structure of a ComponentDefinition object and the manner in which it is encoded. This representation is accomplished by means of the elements property and encoding property.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sequence

owl:Class.tawny:name: Orientation
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Provides values for the orientation of a Sequence entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Orientation

owl:Class.tawny:name: Implementation
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An Implementation represents an instance of a synthetic biological construct, and describes the build phase of a design-built-test-learn workflow. Importantly, an Implementation can be associated with a laboratory sample that was already built, or that is to be built in the future. An Implementation can also represent virtual and simulated instances. An Implementation may be linked back to its original design (either a ModuleDefinition or ComponentDefinition) using the wasDerivedFroms property inherited from the Identified superclass. An Implementation may also link to a ModuleDefinition or ComponentDefinition that specifies its realized structure and/or function.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Implementation

owl:Class.tawny:name: NASequence
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Nucleic acid sequence
owl:Class.rdfs:label: NASequence

owl:Class.tawny:name: Refinement
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Not represented in SBOL directly. It is used in the OWL representation to enforce choosing a refinement using one of its subclasses.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Refinement
sample
owl:Class.tawny:name: sample
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A user SHOULD derive a subset of all possible ComponentDefinition objects specified by CombinatorialDerivation. The manner in which this subset is chosen is for the user to decide.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: oneOrMore
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: At least one Component in the derived ComponentDefinition SHOULD have a wasDerivedFroms property that refers to the template Component.
owl:Class.tawny:name: oneOrMore
Promoter
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Promoter DNA component
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Promoter

owl:Class.tawny:name: mRNA
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: mRNA RNA component
owl:Class.rdfs:label: mRNA
private
owl:Class.tawny:name: private
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a ComponentInstance MUST NOT be referred to by remote MapsTo objects.

owl:Class.tawny:name: RBS
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: RBS DNA component
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RBS

owl:Class.tawny:name: sameOrientationAs
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The subject and object Component objects MUST have the same orientation. If each one is associated with a SequenceAnnotation, then the orientation URIs of the Location objects of the first SequenceAnnotation MUST be among those of the second SequenceAnnotation, and vice versa.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sameOrientationAs

owl:Class.tawny:name: SequenceAnnotation
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The SequenceAnnotation class describes one or more regions of interest on the Sequence objects referred to by its parent ComponentDefinition. In addition, SequenceAnnotation objects can describe the substructure of their parent ComponentDefinition through association with the Component objects contained by this ComponentDefinition.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SequenceAnnotation

owl:Class.tawny:name: SequenceConstraint
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The SequenceConstraint class can be used to assert restrictions on the relative, sequence-based positions of pairs of Component objects contained by the same parent ComponentDefinition. The primary purpose of this class is to enable the specification of partially designed ComponentDefinition objects, for which the precise positions or orientations of their contained Component objects are not yet fully determined. Each SequenceConstraint includes the restriction, subject, and object properties.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SequenceConstraint

owl:Class.tawny:name: RoleIntegration
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Not represented in SBOL directly. It is used in the OWL representation to enforce choosing a role integration using one of its subclasses.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RoleIntegration

owl:Class.tawny:name: ComponentInstance
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The ComponentInstance abstract class is inherited by SBOL classes that represent the usage or occurrence of a ComponentDefinition within a larger design (that is, another ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ComponentInstance

owl:Class.tawny:name: enumerate
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A user SHOULD derive all possible ComponentDefinition objects specified by the CombinatorialDerivation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: enumerate

owl:Class.tawny:name: CDS
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: CDS DNA component
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CDS

owl:Class.tawny:name: CombinatorialDerivation
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The purpose of the CombinatorialDerivation class is to specify combinatorial genetic designs without having to specify every possible design variant. For example, a CombinatorialDerivation can be used to specify a library of reporter gene variants that include different promoters and RBSs without having to specify a ComponentDefinition for every possible combination of promoter, RBS, and CDS in the library. ComponentDefinition objects that realize a CombinatorialDerivation can be derived in accordance with the class properties template, variableComponents, and strategy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CombinatorialDerivation

owl:Class.tawny:name: MapsTo
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: When ComponentDefinition and ModuleDefinition objects are composed into structural and functional hierarchies using ComponentInstance and Module objects, it is often the case that some ComponentInstance objects are intended to represent the same entity in the overall design. The purpose of the MapsTo class is to make these identity relationships clear and explicit. For example, consider a ModuleDefinition for a genetic inverter that includes a FunctionalComponent for an abstract repressor protein. When this ModuleDefinition is instantiated within a “higher level” ModuleDefinition that includes a FunctionalComponent for a LacI protein, the MapsTo object can be used to indicate that the repressor protein in the first ModuleDefinition is LacI in the context of the composite design.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MapsTo
one
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Exactly one Component in the derived ComponentDefinition SHOULD have a wasDerivedFroms property that refers to the template Component.
owl:Class.tawny:name: one
Module
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents the usage or occurrence of a ModuleDefinition within a larger design.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Module

owl:Class.tawny:name: ProteinSequence
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Protein sequence
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ProteinSequence

owl:Class.tawny:name: Protein
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Protein component definition
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Protein

owl:Class.tawny:name: Cut
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Cut class has been introduced to enable the specification of a region between two discrete positions. This specification is accomplished using the at property, which specifies a discrete position that that corresponds to the index of a character in the elements String of a Sequence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cut

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: In the context of the ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition that contains the owner of the MapsTo, all references to the remote ComponentInstance MUST dereference to the local ComponentInstance instead.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: useLocal
owl:Class.tawny:name: useLocal

owl:Class.rdfs:label: verifyIdentical
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the definition properties of the local and remote ComponentInstance objects MUST refer to the same ComponentDefinition.
owl:Class.tawny:name: verifyIdentical
useRemote
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that all references to the local ComponentInstance MUST dereference to the remote ComponentInstance instead.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: useRemote

owl:Class.tawny:name: Model
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Serves as a placeholder for an external computational model and provide additional meta-data to enable better reasoning about the contents of this model.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Model

owl:Class.tawny:name: none
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the FunctionalComponent is neither an input or output.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: none

owl:Class.tawny:name: Collection
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Groups together a set of TopLevel objects that have something in common.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Collection

owl:Class.tawny:name: RNA
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: RNA component definition
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RNA

owl:Class.tawny:name: SBOLVocabulary
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Not represented in SBOL directly. It is used to group SBOL specific terms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SBOLVocabulary

owl:Class.tawny:name: FunctionalComponent
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A FunctionalComponent is an instance of a ComponentDefinition being used as part of a ModuleDefinition. The ModuleDefinition describes how the that describes how the FunctionalComponent interacts with others and summarizes their aggregate function
owl:Class.rdfs:label: FunctionalComponent

owl:Class.tawny:name: Complex
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Complex component definition
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Complex

owl:Class.tawny:name: VariableOperator
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specifies the operator types for combinatorial derivations.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: VariableOperator

owl:Class.tawny:name: Interaction
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Provides more detailed description of how the FunctionalComponent objects of a ModuleDefinition are intended to work together.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Interaction

owl:Class.tawny:name: Direction
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Not represented in SBOL directly. It is used in the OWL representation to enforce choosing a direction type using one of its subclasses.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Direction

owl:Class.tawny:name: differentFrom
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The definition property of the subject Component MUST NOT refer to the same ComponentDefinition as that of the object Component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: differentFrom

owl:Class.tawny:name: SmallMolecule
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: SmallMolecule component definition
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SmallMolecule

owl:Class.tawny:name: out
owl:Class.rdfs:label: out
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the FunctionalComponent is an output.

owl:Class.tawny:name: VariableComponent
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The VariableComponent class can be used to specify a choice of ComponentDefinition objects for any new 35 Component derived from a template Component in the template ComponentDefinition.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: VariableComponent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the FunctionalComponent is an input.
owl:Class.tawny:name: in
owl:Class.rdfs:label: in

owl:Class.tawny:name: Access
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Not represented in SBOL directly. It is used in the OWL representation to enforce choosing an access type using one of its subclasses.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Access

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: isModuleOf
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse of the module property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isModuleOf

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: location
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The location property is REQUIRED to specify one or more Location objects that indicate which elements of a Sequence are described by the SequenceAnnotation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: location

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: functionalComponent
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The property is OPTIONAL and MAY be used specify a set of FunctionalComponent objects contained by the ModuleDefinition.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: functionalComponent

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: operator
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The operator property is REQUIRED and has a data type of URI. This property specifies how many Component objects SHOULD be derived from the template Component during the derivation of a new ComponentDefinition.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: operator

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: variantDerivation
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The variantDerivations property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain zero or more URIs that each refer to a CombinatorialDerivation. This property enables the convenient specification of ComponentDefinition objects derived in accordance with another CombinatorialDerivation to serve as options when deriving a new Component from the template Component.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: variantDerivation

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: persistentIdentity
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: It is used to refer to a set of SBOL objects that are different versions of each other.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: persistentIdentity

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: refinement
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The refinement property is REQUIRED and has a data type of URI. Each MapsTo object MUST specify the rela- 27 tionship between its local and remote ComponentInstance objects.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: refinement

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: access
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The access property is a REQUIRED URI that indicates whether the ComponentInstance can be referred to remotely by a MapsTo on another ComponentInstance or Module contained by a different parent ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition (one that does not contain this ComponentInstance)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: access

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: role
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Clarifies the potential function of an entity in a biochemical or physical context. When it is used for ComponentDefinitions, it MUST identify terms from ontologies that are consistent with the types property of the ComponentDefinition. For example, the roles property of a DNA or RNA ComponentDefinition could contain URIs identifying terms from the Sequence Ontology (SO).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: role

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: variableComponent
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The variableComponent property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain a set of VariableComponent objects.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: variableComponent

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: isObjectOf
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse of the object property
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isObjectOf

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: roleIntegration
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A roleIntegration specifies the relationship between a Component instance’s own set of roles and the set of roles on the included sub-ComponentDefinition.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: roleIntegration

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: sequenceConstraint
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The sequenceConstraints property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain a set of SequenceConstraint objects. These objects describe any restrictions on the relative, sequence-based positions and/or orientations of the Component objects contained by the ComponentDefinition. For example, the ComponentDefinition of a gene might specify that the position of its promoter Component precedes that of its CDS Component. This is particularly useful when a ComponentDefinition lacks a Sequence and therefore cannot specify the precise, sequence-based positions of its Component objects using SequenceAnnotation objects.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sequenceConstraint

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: model
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The model property is OPTIONAL and MAY be used to specify a set of URI references to Model objects.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: model

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: orientation
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the type of a component's orientation. All subclasses of Location share this property, which can be used to indicate how the region specified by the SequenceAnnotation and any associated double-stranded Component is oriented on the elements of a Sequence from their parent ComponentDefinition
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: orientation

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: mapsTo
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The mapsTo property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain a MapsTo object that refers to and links together a ComponentInstance object (both Component objects and FunctionalComponent objects) within a larger design.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: mapsTo

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: language
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The language property is REQUIRED and MUST contain a URI that specifies the language in which the model is implemented. It is RECOMMENDED that this URI refer to a term from the EMBRACE Data and Methods (EDAM) ontology.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: language

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: participation
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The participation property is an OPTIONAL and MAY contain a Participation object, which identifies the roles that its referenced FunctionalComponent plays in the Interaction.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: participation

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: framework
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The framework property is REQUIRED and MUST contain a URI that specifies the framework in which the model is implemented. It is RECOMMENDED this URI refer to a term from the modeling framework branch of the SBO when possible.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: framework

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: restriction
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The restriction property is REQUIRED and has a data type of URI. This property MUST indicate the type of structural restriction on the positions, orientations, or structural identities of the subject and object Component objects in relation to each other.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: restriction

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: isInteractionOf
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse of the interaction property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isInteractionOf

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: component
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The components property is OPTIONAL and MAY specify a set of Component objects that are contained by the ComponentDefinition. The set of relations between Component and ComponentDefinition objects is strictly acyclic.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: component

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: member
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Contains a reference to a top level entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: member

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: type
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the category of biochemical or physical entity. For example DNA, protein, or small molecule that a ComponentDefinition object abstracts for the purpose of engineering design. For DNA or RNA entities, additional types fields are used to describe nucleic acid topology (circular / linear) and strandedness (double- or single-stranded).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: type

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: isSubjectOf
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse of the subject property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isSubjectOf

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: participant
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The participant property MUST specify precisely one FunctionalComponent object that plays the designated role in its parent Interaction object.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: participant

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: isMemberOf
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse of the member property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isMemberOf

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: module
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The property is OPTIONAL and MAY be used specify a set of Module objects contained by the ModuleDefinition. Note that the set of relations between Module and ModuleDefinition objects is strictly acyclic.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: module

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: built
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The built property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain a URI that MUST refer to a TopLevel object that is either a ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition. This ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition is intended to describe the actual physical structure and/or functional behavior of the Implementation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: built

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: source
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The source property is REQUIRED and MUST contain a URI reference to the source file for a model.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: source

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: interaction
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The interaction property is OPTIONAL and MAY be used specify a set of Interaction objects within the ModuleDefinition.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: interaction

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: strategy
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates combinatorial derivation strategy.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: strategy

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: isDefinitionOf
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse of the definition property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isDefinitionOf

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: object
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The object property is REQUIRED and MUST contain a URI that refers to a Component contained by the same parent ComponentDefinition that contains the SequenceConstraint. This Component MUST NOT be the same Component that the SequenceConstraint refers to via its subject property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: object

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: subject
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The subject property is REQUIRED and MUST contain a URI that refers to a Component contained by the same parent ComponentDefinition that contains the SequenceConstraint.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: subject

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: local
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This REQUIRED property has a data type of URI and is used to refer to the ComponentInstance contained by the “higher level” ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition. This local ComponentInstance MUST be contained by the ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition that contains the ComponentInstance or Module that owns the MapsTo.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: local

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: variable
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The variable property is REQUIRED and MUST contain a URI that refers to a template Component in the template ComponentDefinition.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: variable

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: definition
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The definition property is a REQUIRED URI that refers to the ComponentDefinition of the ComponentInstance. As described in the previous section, this ComponentDefinition effectively provides information about the types and roles of the ComponentInstance.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: definition

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: template
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The template property is REQUIRED and MUST contain a URI that refers to a ComponentDefinition. This ComponentDefinition is expected to serve as a template for the derivation of new ComponentDefinition objects.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: template

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: encoding
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The encoding property is REQUIRED and has a data type of URI. This property MUST indicate how the elements property of a Sequence MUST be formed and interpreted.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: encoding

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: variant
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The variants property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain zero or more URIs that each refer to a ComponentDefinition. This property specifies individual ComponentDefinition objects to serve as options when deriving a new Component from the template Component.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: variant

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: remote
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This REQUIRED property has a data type of URI and is used to refer to the ComponentInstance contained by the “lower level” ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition. This remote ComponentInstance MUST be contained by the ComponentDefinition or ModuleDefinition that is the definition of the ComponentInstance or Module that owns the MapsTo. Lastly, the access property of the remote ComponentInstance MUST be set to “public.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: remote

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: isSequenceOf
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse of the sequence property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isSequenceOf

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: variantCollection
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain zero or more URIs that each refer to a Collection. The members property of each Collection referred to in this way MUST NOT be empty. This property enables the convenient specification of existing groups of ComponentDefinition objects to serve as options when deriving a new Component from the template Component.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: variantCollection

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: direction
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Each FunctionalComponent MUST specify via the direction property whether it serves as an input, output, both, or neither for its parent ModuleDefinition object.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: direction

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: sequenceAnnotation
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The sequenceAnnotations property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain a set of SequenceAnnotation objects. Each SequenceAnnotation specifies and describes a potentially discontiguous region on the Sequence objects referred to by the ComponentDefinition.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sequenceAnnotation

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: isComponentOf
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse of the component property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isComponentOf

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: format
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The format property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain a URI that specifies the format of the attached file. It is RECOMMENDED that this URI refer to a term from the EMBRACE Data and Methods (EDAM) ontology
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: format

owl:ObjectProperty.tawny:name: sequence
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The sequences property is OPTIONAL and MAY include a set of URIs that refer to Sequence objects. These objects define the primary structure of the ComponentDefinition.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sequence

owl:DatatypeProperty.tawny:name: end
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the inclusive ending position of the Range.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: end

owl:DatatypeProperty.tawny:name: hash
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The hash property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain a SHA-1 hash of the file contents represented as a hexadecimal digest.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hash

owl:DatatypeProperty.tawny:name: start
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the inclusive starting position of the Range.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: start

owl:DatatypeProperty.tawny:name: size
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The size property is OPTIONAL and MAY contain a long indicating the file size in bytes.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: size

owl:DatatypeProperty.tawny:name: displayId
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The displayId property is an OPTIONAL identifier with a data type of String. This property is intended to be an intermediate between name and identity that is machine-readable, but more human-readable than the full URI of an identity.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: displayId

owl:DatatypeProperty.tawny:name: elements
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The elements property is a REQUIRED String of characters that represents the constituents of a biological or chemical molecule. For example, these characters could represent the nucleotide bases of a molecule of DNA, the amino acid residues of a protein, or the atoms and chemical bonds of a small molecule.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: elements

owl:DatatypeProperty.tawny:name: version
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The version property is OPTIONAL and has a data type of String. This property can be used to compare two SBOL objects with the same persistentIdentity.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: version

owl:DatatypeProperty.tawny:name: at
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: specifies a discrete position that that corresponds to the index of a character in the elements String of a Sequence.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: at

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The PLlac 0-1 promoter is a hybrid regulatory region consisting of the promoter P(L) of phage lambda with the cI binding sites replaced with lacO1. The hybrid design allows for strong promotion that can nevertheless be tightly repressed by LacI, the Lac inhibitor (i.e. repressor) (BBa_C0010) ([LUTZ97]). The activity of the promoter can be regulated over a >600-fold range by IPTG in E.Coli DH5-alpha-Z1 (same paper reference).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
hybrid promoter design to create strong promoter that is, at the same time, highly repressible. note that the upstream operator installed in this hybrid is slightly different than the one in the original source (Lutz and Bujard, 1997). the most upstream operator region is slightly truncated in the represillator version, so that both operators in the hybrid are the same sequence. see references for details. also, the sequence has been truncated after the transcriptional start site.

LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and increase transcription. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Neelaksh Varshney, Grace Kenney, Daniel Shen, Samantha Sutton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lacI+pL

prov:Agent.dcterms:description: SBOLDesigner is a simple, biologist-friendly CAD software tool for creating and manipulating the sequences of genetic constructs using the Synthetic Biology Open Language (SBOL) 2.0 data model. Throughout the design process, SBOL Visual symbols, a system of schematic glyphs, provide standardized visualizations of individual parts. SBOLDesigner completes a workflow for users of genetic design automation tools. It combines a simple user interface with the power of the SBOL standard and serves as a launchpad for more detailed designs involving simulations and experiments. Some new features in SBOLDesigner are SynBioHub integration, local repositories, importing of parts/sequences from existing files, import and export of GenBank and FASTA files, extended role ontology support, the ability to partially open designs with multiple root ComponentDefinitions, backward compatibility with SBOL 1.1, and versioning.
prov:Agent.dc:creator: Sean Sleight
John Gennari
prov:Agent.dcterms:title: SBOLDesigner CAD Tool

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Cyan fluorescent protein (ECFP) reporter coding sequence without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_E0022 cyan fluorescent protein is based on BioBrick part BBa_E0021. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
